    Marshall Emberton II

    Merchant Video

    SUPERIOR SIGNATURE SOUND

    Emberton II delivers sound that is rich, clear and loud, like the artist intended. Experience absolute 360° sound with True Stereophonic, a unique form of multi-directional sound from Marshall – where every spot is a sweet spot.

    30+ HOURS OF PORTABLE PLAYTIME

    Emberton II offers 30+ hours of portable playtime on a single charge. Its compact size, rugged durability and reliable playtime make it perfect to take with you. When you’re out of battery, Emberton II won’t keep you waiting long – plug in your speaker and return to full battery in 3 hours.

    ROADWORTHY DESIGN RATED IPX7

    Emberton II is tough and resilient, boasting an extremely durable and easy-to-use design that features an IP67 dust- and water-resistance rating. It won’t let rain or dirt get in the way of your music.

    How are ratings calculated?
    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    • avik331
      5.0 out of 5 stars Absolutely amazing!!! But not for everyone
      Reviewed in India on 20 August 2024
      Style Name: Emberton 2Verified Purchase
      Battery: Just received it today and charged it to full and since then have been using it non-stop atleast 9 hours now and only 2 bars went down. Until impressions of battery is excellent.

      Build: Excellent! Nothing else will describe it better. I also have a Marshall Willen and this is even better. The Willen excellent for travel and using it in the Airbnb or a hotel room. Even this although it's over 700g it's still worth carrying in your backpack.

      Sound: The sound quality is brilliant and sometimes it's just mesmerizing. Although the bass does gets lost over 80% volume but it's not totally bad. The sound is not that of a party speaker with a lot of bass, instead for a chill session. Like having some beers and wine with your 4-5 friends in the terrace or balcony. The sound is room filling and it's great for me. The sound is tuned for rock, classic rock, alternative and similar genre. It's also great for Indian oldies and you will love the output of in these kinda scenarios. For bass junkies and groovy party people, stay away! It's not meant for you and won't enjoy the sound output.
      It's also great for watching a movie in your iPad, the sound out is great with excellent voice and associated sound.

      Price: I got it for 13k will credit card and all bells and whistles of discount and it does justify its price for me. Over that around 15k I don't think it's worth it.

      Regret: Onky regret I have is that today itself the Marshall Emberton 3 got released for a couple of thousand more and 2 years warranty in Marshall.com in India. May be I could have taken a couple of days to order I could have the never one. But the sound quality makes me so happy, I don't feel like returning this Emberton2
      Try listening to any song of the movie Rockstar and with A R Rehman's best creation and you will feel like hugging the speakers for its sound quality.

      Conclusion: If you can buy the newer version with better features and newer Bluetooth 5.3LE with very little battery consumption and better sound output and new Dynamic Sound optimisation. But if you want to save some money and feel like buying this and have the sound genres mentioned above, go for it. You will love it👍

    • Ricardo
      5.0 out of 5 stars Buen sonido, claro y nítido, buenos bajos
      Reviewed in Mexico on 18 March 2024
      Style Name: Emberton 2Verified Purchase
      Definitivamente estas bocinas Bluetooth valen lo que cuestan. Una buena marca y buen sonido, si tienes dos y las pones en modo de apilamiento o stack se escuchan perfectas, fuerte y claro. Esos detalles de el sonido de la guitarra cuando enciende y cuando se apaga que hacen distintivo a la marca me parecen excelentes, para escuchar heavy metal son perfectas, pero también para escuchar música clásica, pop, electrónica, igual ver películas, tengo un monitor de pantalla ancha y se oyen perfectos los bajos.

      El único detalle que no me gusto es que no se pueden poner en modo estéreo o sea una a la izquierda y otra a la derecha y cada una reproduzca un canal, para eso compré el par hehe, pero ni modo las dos se escuchan en estéreo así es que la única manera que las oigo es en modo apilamiento o stack.

      No se batallan para el emparejamiento, solo que como no se conectan en stereo solo se conecta una y de ahí pues hay que presionar el botón de la principal 3 veces y la otra dos veces cada que las conecto para escuchar las dos. Fuera de eso tiene un buen sonido y son de calidad, solo que al subir completamente el volumen tienen una muy pequeña distorsión pero es muy mínima.

      Fuera de esos dos detalles es una muy buena marca y tiene un excelente sonido. Las recomiendo sin dudarlo.

      Nota: no recomiendo actualizar el firmware del dispositivo, yo lo hice en una bocina y su sonido pasó de ser claro y nítido a un sonido encerrado, soso y nada preciso. Después de eso lo restauré a las condiciones de salida de fábrica y todo perfecto volvió a tener el sonido fuerte y claro de cómo nuevo.

      Reviewed in Mexico on 18 March 2024
      Definitivamente estas bocinas Bluetooth valen lo que cuestan. Una buena marca y buen sonido, si tienes dos y las pones en modo de apilamiento o stack se escuchan perfectas, fuerte y claro.       No se batallan para el emparejamiento, solo que como no se conectan en stereo solo se conecta una y de ahí pues hay que presionar el botón de la principal 3 veces y la otra dos veces cada que las conecto para escuchar las dos.
